This paper addresses the problem of unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel method that uses domain adversarial learning and two new techniques to address negative transfer and uncertainty propagation. These techniques are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, since the paper focuses on image classification tasks, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
